{{redirect|Geospatial}}
'''Geographic data and information''' are defined in the [[ISO/TC 211]] series of standards as data and information having an implicit or explicit association with a location relative to the Earth.<ref> [http://www.isotc211.org/Terminology.htm ISO/TC 211 Multi-Lingual Glossary of Terms]</ref>

It is also called '''geospatial data and information''',{{cn|date=July 2016}} '''[[Georeferencing|georeferenced]] data and information''',{{cn|date=July 2016}} as well as '''geodata''' and '''geoinformation'''.{{cn|date=July 2016}}

Approximately 90% of government sourced data has a location component.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Romero|first1=Melissa|url=https://philly.curbed.com/2017/11/7/16617296/philadelphia-properties-land-vacant-lot-atlas-map-tool|website=Curbed|accessdate=7 November 2017}}</ref>
