{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2017}}
{{Barack Obama sidebar}}
This is a '''list of international presidential trips made by Barack Obama''', the [[List of Presidents of the United States|44th]] [[President of the United States|president]] of the [[United States]]. [[Barack Obama]] made 52 international trips to 58 different countries (in addition to visiting the [[West Bank]]) during his [[Presidency of Barack Obama|presidency]], which began on [[First inauguration of Barack Obama|January 20, 2009]] and ended on [[Inauguration of Donald Trump|January 20, 2017]]. He set the record as the most-traveled president for any first year in office. Obama made ten trips to 21 countries (four countries were visited twice) and was out of the U.S. a total of 40 days.
[[File:Barack Obama foreign trips.png|thumb|center|260px|World map highlighting countries visited by Barack Obama while president]]

The number of visits per country where he traveled are:
* One visit to [[Argentina]], [[Brazil]], [[Cambodia]], [[Chile]], [[Colombia]], [[Costa Rica]], [[Cuba]], [[Egypt]], [[El Salvador]], [[Estonia]], [[Ethiopia]], [[Ghana]], [[Greece]], [[Iraq]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], [[Jamaica]], [[Jordan]], [[Kenya]], [[Laos]], [[Netherlands]], [[Norway]], [[Panama]], [[Peru]], [[Portugal]], [[Senegal]], [[Singapore]], [[Spain]], [[Sweden]], [[Tanzania]], [[Thailand]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]], [[Vietnam]] and the [[West Bank]]
* Two visits to [[Australia]], [[Belgium]], [[Czech Republic]], [[Denmark]], [[India]], [[Indonesia]], [[Israel]], [[Italy]], [[Malaysia]], [[Myanmar]], [[Philippines]], [[Russia]], [[South Africa]], [[Turkey]] and [[Vatican City]]
* Three visits to [[Canada]], [[China]] and [[Poland]]
* Four visits to [[Afghanistan]], [[Japan]], [[Saudi Arabia]] and [[South Korea]]
* Five visits to [[Mexico]] and the [[United Kingdom]]
* Six visits to [[France]] and [[Germany]]

